<article class="post-1459 post type-post status-publish format-standard category-ontario-oil-gas-salt-resources-library entry override" itemscope="itemscope" itemtype="http://schema.org/BlogPosting"><header class="entry-header"><h2 class="entry-title"><a href="http://www.ontariopetroleuminstitute.com/ontario-oil-industry-featured-in-fairbank-oil-story/">Ontario oil industry featured in Fairbank Oil story</a></h2></header><div class="entry-content"><p>The Toronto Star published a feature article “Oil booming just down Hwy. 401”on Fairbank Oil Properties in the paper’s Business Section on March 9th.   The Star ran the feature from a story on the Ontario industry written by Bloomberg News.   The Toronto Star can be read by going to the following link. www.pressreader.com/canada/toronto-star/20160310/282449938124143</p>
</div></article><article class="post-1456 post type-post status-publish format-standard category-ontario-oil-gas-salt-resources-library entry override" itemscope="itemscope" itemtype="http://schema.org/BlogPosting"><header class="entry-header"><h2 class="entry-title"><a href="http://www.ontariopetroleuminstitute.com/wsbop-training-april-18-21-2016/">WSBOP Training April 18-21, 2016</a></h2></header><div class="entry-content"><p>A four day Well Service Blow Out Prevention course is scheduled for April 18-21 in London.  Fill out the registration form if your require this training. WSBOPtraining &#8211; 2016 &nbsp;</p>
</div></article><article class="post-1444 post type-post status-publish format-standard category-ontario-oil-gas-salt-resources-library entry override" itemscope="itemscope" itemtype="http://schema.org/BlogPosting"><header class="entry-header"><h2 class="entry-title"><a href="http://www.ontariopetroleuminstitute.com/h2s-alive-training-april-4th/">H2S Alive Training &#8211; May 2nd</a></h2></header><div class="entry-content"><p>We have scheduled another H2S Alive Training course for Monday, May 2nd being held at Union Gas Limited in Chatham.  The course for April 4th in London has been cancelled.  H2S-May 2, 2016</p>
</div></article><article class="post-1402 post type-post status-publish format-standard category-ontario-oil-gas-salt-resources-library entry override" itemscope="itemscope" itemtype="http://schema.org/BlogPosting"><header class="entry-header"><h2 class="entry-title"><a href="http://www.ontariopetroleuminstitute.com/canadas-edge-is-resources/">Canada’s edge is resources</a></h2></header><div class="entry-content"><p>Despite all of the best intentions of society generally and the political leadership in Canada to focus attention on the effects of climate change the country’s natural resources, oil and natural gas in particular, provide Canada with an edge when you consider our economic future. Gordon Gibson, columnist, author, and former politician from British Columbia, [&hellip;]</p>
</div></article></div></section>
